Date: Fri, 20 Mar 2026 18:35:43 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 028/174] =?UTF-8?q?PGCL:=20fix=20shared=20library=20mmap?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20=E2=80=94=20use=20MMUPAGE=20granularity=20in=20arch=20sys=5F?=
 =?UTF-8?q?mmap=20wrappers?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Arch-specific sys_mmap/mmap2 syscall wrappers check file offset alignment
against PAGE_MASK/PAGE_SIZE and convert to page offsets via PAGE_SHIFT.
With PGCL (PAGE_SIZE=64KB, MMUPAGE_SIZE=4KB), this rejects valid 4KB-aligned
offsets from the dynamic linker when mmap()ing shared library LOAD segments,
breaking all dynamically-linked binaries on arm64 and riscv64.

Fix all 11 arch wrappers (arm64, arm64-compat, riscv, loongarch, microblaze,
mips, csky, parisc, sh, sparc32, sparc64) to use MMUPAGE_MASK/MMUPAGE_SHIFT.
Also fix mm/util.c vm_mmap overflow check (PAGE_ALIGN→MMUPAGE_ALIGN) and
fs/binfmt_elf.c MMAP_PAGE_ZERO mapping size (PAGE_SIZE→MMUPAGE_SIZE).

Tested: arm64 and riscv64 now successfully run dynamically-linked Alpine
musl binaries. x86_64/arm64/riscv64 all pass 23/23+ PGCL tests.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
